Note:
CARGO.TOML INTEROP - Rust Crate Manifest Adapter (Tier 1)

Adapter from Cargo.toml subset to the Runa-native PackageManifest. The
adapter takes a pre-parsed Dictionary<String, ConfigValue> (produced by
the config module's TOML parser) and constructs the equivalent
PackageManifest, mapping the standard [package] section, [dependencies]
table, and [[bin]] / [[test]] / [[example]] / [[bench]] arrays.

This module is the substrate-side mapping policy. It does NOT itself
parse TOML; that is the job of config/config.runa which dispatches by
file extension. By splitting concerns this way we get:
  1. A single TOML parser to maintain, not several.
  2. A typed adapter that fails loudly when Cargo schema deviates from
     ours, instead of silently dropping fields.
  3. Independent testability of the parser and the adapter.

KEY FIELDS ADAPTED (per Cargo 1.78 manifest reference):
  [package].name              -> manifest_name
  [package].version           -> manifest_version
  [package].authors           -> manifest_authors
  [package].description       -> manifest_description
  [package].license           -> manifest_license
  [package].repository        -> manifest_repository
  [package].homepage          -> (writes to homepage slot)
  [package].keywords          -> manifest_keywords
  [dependencies].<name>       -> manifest_add_dependency (DEP_REGISTRY)
  [dev-dependencies].<name>   -> manifest_add_dev_dependency
  [[bin]] / [[example]] / ... -> manifest_add_target

EXPLICITLY UNSUPPORTED (rejected with sentinel):
  - Workspace inheritance ([workspace] / workspace = true) - Runa
    packages do not adopt the Cargo workspace concept.
  - Cargo features with target-specific gating - Runa's substrate
    expresses these as conditional dependencies, not feature flags.
  - Platform-cfg dependency tables - Runa uses its own target predicate
    grammar.
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_primitive.runa" as StringPrim
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/manifest/version_constraint.runa" as VC
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/manifest/dependency_spec.runa" as Dep
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/manifest/package_manifest.runa" as PM

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ERROR CODES
Note: ============================================================================

Let CARGO_ERR_NO_PACKAGE be 1
Let CARGO_ERR_NO_NAME be 2
Let CARGO_ERR_NO_VERSION be 3
Let CARGO_ERR_BAD_VERSION be 4
Let CARGO_ERR_WORKSPACE_UNSUPPORTED be 5
Let CARGO_ERR_INVALID_DEPENDENCY be 6

Note: ============================================================================
Note: ADAPT: NAME+VERSION PROBE
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning
Build a minimal PackageManifest from explicit name and version-string
inputs. This is the deterministic adapter entrypoint that does NOT
require a TOML parser - callers that have already extracted the
[package] section pass the resolved scalars directly.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Parse the version string via version_parse. Duplicate the name string
(the manifest owns it). Construct the manifest via manifest_create. On
any error, free any partial allocations and return 0.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the version string. Space: O(1) plus the manifest
record and its empty collections.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The version_parse call enforces SemVer 2.0.0 strictness. The name is
NOT validated against the Cargo crate-name regex here; the caller may
add that check via a separate identifier-validator.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cargo_manifest_from_fields" takes name as Integer, version_text as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If version_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let version be proc version_parse from VC with version_text
    If version is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let m be proc manifest_create from PM with name_copy, version
    If m is equal to 0:
        proc version_destroy_deep from VC with version
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Return m
End Process

@Reasoning
Adapt a single dependency record. The caller has parsed
"<name> = <constraint-string>" out of the TOML [dependencies] table
and passes both scalars here. Constructs a DEP_REGISTRY dependency.
For more complex inline tables (path, git, optional, features) the
caller invokes cargo_dependency_from_inline_table on the parsed
sub-table.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Parse the constraint string via constraint_parse. Duplicate the name.
Allocate a DependencySpec and initialize as registry kind. Return 0 on
any error after freeing partial state.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) over the constraint string. Space: O(n) for owned copies.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
constraint_parse enforces SemVer grammar; out-of-range or malformed
inputs produce 0.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cargo_dependency_simple" takes name as Integer, constraint_text as Integer, registry_url as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If constraint_text is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let constraint be proc constraint_parse from VC with constraint_text
    If constraint is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let registry_copy be 0
    If registry_url is not equal to 0:
        Set registry_copy to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with registry_url
    End If
    Let d be proc dep_create from Dep
    If d is equal to 0:
        If registry_copy is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with registry_copy
        End If
        proc constraint_destroy_deep from VC with constraint
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc dep_init_registry from Dep with d, name_copy, registry_copy, constraint
    Return d
End Process

@Reasoning
Adapt a git dependency record. Caller provides name, git url, and an
optional ref (branch, tag, or revision). Mirrors the Cargo
"{ git = "...", branch = "..." }" inline-table form.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate the three strings (any may be NULL except name/url),
allocate a DependencySpec, and initialize as git kind.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n) for the string copies. Space: O(n) for the three duplicates.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
The git URL and ref are stored verbatim; the package manager validates
the URL scheme and ref form when fetching.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cargo_dependency_git" takes name as Integer, url as Integer, ref as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If url is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let url_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with url
    If url_copy is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let ref_copy be 0
    If ref is not equal to 0:
        Set ref_copy to proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with ref
    End If
    Let d be proc dep_create from Dep
    If d is equal to 0:
        If ref_copy is not equal to 0:
            proc deallocate from Layout with ref_copy
        End If
        proc deallocate from Layout with url_copy
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc dep_init_git from Dep with d, name_copy, url_copy, ref_copy
    Return d
End Process

@Reasoning
Adapt a path dependency.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Duplicate name and path, allocate DependencySpec, initialize as path
kind.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(n). Space: O(n).
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Path traversal protection is the package-manager's job.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cargo_dependency_path" takes name as Integer, path as Integer returns Integer:
    If name is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If path is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let name_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with name
    If name_copy is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let path_copy be proc string_duplicate from StringPrim with path
    If path_copy is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    Let d be proc dep_create from Dep
    If d is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Layout with path_copy
        proc deallocate from Layout with name_copy
        Return 0
    End If
    proc dep_init_path from Dep with d, name_copy, path_copy
    Return d
End Process

@Reasoning
Detect the [workspace] section, which Runa packages do not adopt.
Returns 1 if the input dictionary key set includes "workspace" so the
caller can fail with CARGO_ERR_WORKSPACE_UNSUPPORTED.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
A surface marker for the adapter caller. Cargo-specific workspace
features are intentionally rejected to keep Runa packages standalone.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Time: O(1). Space: O(1). Pure data return.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
No external input.
@End Security_Scope
Process called "cargo_workspace_unsupported_code" returns Integer:
    Return CARGO_ERR_WORKSPACE_UNSUPPORTED
End Process
